The paper deals with distribution testing, which is a topic in computer science that falls under several sub-categories. The focus on memory and communication constraints suggests that the paper may belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of information theory techniques for analyzing the communication complexity of the protocols suggests that the paper may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of statistical techniques for testing distributions suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The focus on communication complexity suggests that the paper may also belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the use of distributed models suggests that the paper may belong to the systems and control (cs.SI) sub-category.
